subSubSection.paragraph: This species is widely distributed in central and eastern North America. It was recorded from four provinces in Canada (MB, NS, ON, QC) by Fernandez-Triana (2010) , but no locality records were provided at that time. Recently four more Canadian provinces and territories (AB, NB, NT, SK) and one state (AK) from the United States were added ( Fernandez-Triana et al. 2014 ). Here we present additional information about the distribution of this species in the Nearctic, including two new provincial records for Canada (NL, PE) and one state (FL) from the United States, based on examined specimens from the BIO and CNC collections. Data for those specimens was extracted from BOLD.

The specimens of A. ensiger that rendered DNA barcodes comprise two BINS, BOLD:ACE6783 (ON, MB) and BOLD:AAA3764 (AB, ON, SK and some localities of southern US) (Suppl. material 4); whether they represent two different species or not will be studied in an upcoming paper.
